                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/421: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-10-20T11:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 20, 1926—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 20—4:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>495. Your 234, October 16, 4 p.m. I am deferring action contemplated in third
                    paragraph my 485, October 16, 1 p.m., in view of <pb facs="1015" n="883"
                        xml:id="pg_883"/> diplomatic body meeting called for this morning further to
                    discuss Canton tax situation in particular relation to certain instructions from
                    his Government which the British Minister, I understand, intends then to bring
                    to our attention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
